!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

beach /biːtʃ/

(beaching,beached,beaches) 

1. N-COUNT A beach is an area of sand or stones beside the ocean. 海滩 

例： ...a beautiful sandy beach. …一片美丽的沙滩。 

2. V-T/V-I If something such as a boat beaches , or if it is beached , it is pulled or forced out of the water and onto land. 使上岸; 上岸 

例： We beached the canoe, running it right up the bank. 我们把独木舟拖上了海滩，直朝堤岸拖去。 

例： The boat beached on a mud flat. 船在泥沼上搁浅了。

